poems.content:
She came like spring,
With a crown of flowers;
She passed by like summer,
With sun-like eyes,
Reminding me of sunshine;
Sweating like monsoon,
She made my heart wet like rains of June;
Melodiously rustling maple leaves,
She walked into the autumn,
With skin like cotton;
She cooled off like pre-winter,
Diving into the river;
She hushed with ease,
Like winter breeze,
She smiled at me,
And got my heart seized.
